Moved 'Single Path' up to test/validator 4. Now paired with the 'All Colour Tests' which I think works well.

@Timinator: Can I ask about your longest execution times and which test/validator they correspond to? (Including the 3 new testing validators)

Also does anyone know what the actual time limit is? I.e. is it 3s to read in the inputs and 2s after the last input is read or? How does it work exactly...

@Harry.B.
Thank you for the visual examples. I'm guessing that "already drawn paths" might actually *reduce* the difficulty, since they restrict the available choices for which paths to try?

"Blockers" are slightly interesting for the reason you mentioned, while "breakable/destructible blocks" look very interesting.

@Timinator
@Harry.B. brought up "heuristic" and "order of search" (NESW). How relevant are those points for your Algorithm X solution?
